<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_kʼardīw" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>kʼardīw</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kʼardew</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>обрыв</q></cit></sense><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>kʼardīwy ræbyn bajjæfton ærtæ saw ændærǵy</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>у подножия обрыва я настиг три силуэта</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>I caught three silhouettes at the foot of the cliff</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>10</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>kʼardīwy ræbyn bajjæfton ærtæ saw ændærǵy</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>у подножия обрыва я настиг три силуэта</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>I caught three silhouettes at the foot of the cliff</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>10</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Термины, связанные с горной природой, идут в осетинском обычно из кавказских языков (см. <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>51, 49</biblScope></bibl>). Можно думать, что и %ikʼardew%i представляет субстратное слово, родственное <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"><lang/><w>k’ərde, k’irde</w><gloss><q>скала</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>k’lde</w></mentioned>).</etym><etym xml:lang="en">In Ossetic, the terms, related to mountain nature, are usually borrowed from Caucasian languages (see <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>51, 49</biblScope></bibl>). One may think that %ikʼardew%i is also a substrate word, which is cognate to <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"><lang/><w>k’ərde, k’irde</w><gloss><q>cliff</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>k’lde</w></mentioned>).</etym></entry>